    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-21T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-21T11:00:00-05:00" n="564"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/520</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-21T12:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1918, noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1656. Legation’s 3059, June 5, 6 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d564fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> War Trade Board with approval of Department has determined
                    to enter into definite relations with Netherlands Oversea Trust so that all
                    commodities exported from the United States to Holland, with such exceptions as
                    may be agreed upon, will be consigned to the Netherlands Oversea Trust, which
                    Trust in turn will undertake to give adequate guarantee that commodities so
                    consigned to it will be utilized for purposes intended by the United States in
                    permitting export to Holland. You are authorized to discuss the foregoing
                    informally with the appropriate officials of the Netherlands Oversea Trust, and
                    you will cable your views as to the character and form of undertakings which
                    should be given by the Trust.</p>
                <p>Repeat to London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
